gmd:abstract.gco:CharacterString: INDUSTRIAL_PARKS_INDOT_IN is a point shapefile that shows industrial park locations in Indiana. It is derived from data provided by personnel of the Indiana Department of Transportation (INDOT). This data set is a composite of data obtained from different sources. For some facilities, the source of locational data is unknown. For other facilities, address matching was used to obtain locations. And in some places, the centriods of zip-code areas and (or) counties are used. Consequently, points may be located several miles from the actual facility. Therefore, this data set is intended for general use only, and is not intended to replace an on-the-ground survey.

gmd:purpose.gco:CharacterString: This data was developed to provide general information regarding industrial parks to the public in the form of a GIS layer.

gmd:description.gco:CharacterString: Personnel of the Indiana Geological Survey (IGS) received the Microsoft Excel spreadsheet GISLAYER2BLOOMINGTON.XLS from INDOT personnel on June 2, 2006. This spreadsheet contained locational information for industrial parks in decimal degrees. This spreadsheet was saved as a comma-delimited text file and loaded into ESRI ArcGIS 9.1. The ESRI ArcMap command titled "Display XY Data" was then used to display this data, and then it was saved to an ESRI shapefile named INDUSTRIAL_PARKS_DecDeg. The shapefile was then projected into Universal Transverse Mercator (UTM), Zone 16, NAD83 using ESRI ArcToolbox, and saved as INDUSTRIAL_PARKS_INDOT_IN. The field titled "IndustPark" was deleted from the attribute file for INDUSTRIAL_PARKS_INDOT_IN.

This metadata was pre-parsed and parsed using CNS (Chew and Spit v 2.6.1) and MP (Metadata Parser v 2.7.1) software written by Peter N. Schweitzer (U.S. Geological Survey). The errors generated by MP were all addressed and corrected, except that no values were assigned to "Abscissa_Resolution" and "Ordinate_Resolution."
